## Build Order — Phased

### Phase 1 — Skeleton (1h)

- [ ] `pyproject.toml` with project metadata, deps, console_scripts entry for `wok`
- [ ] Empty modules with docstrings
- [ ] `wok --version` works
- [ ] `wok run path.wok` parses CLI args (does nothing yet)
- **Checkpoint:** `pip install -e .` succeeds; `wok --help` shows usage. Commit.

### Phase 2 — Lexer (2h)

- [ ] `Token` dataclass: `kind`, `value`, `line`, `col`
- [ ] `lex(source: str) -> list[Token]`
- [ ] INDENT/DEDENT handling (track indent stack)
- [ ] NEWLINE tokens
- [ ] Unit + number combination (`200g` → `NUMBER(200) UNIT(g)` or single `QUANTITY` token — your call, document it)
- [ ] `test_lexer.py`: 10+ cases including malformed input
- **Checkpoint:** lexing `pad_thai.wok` produces a sensible token stream. Commit.

### Phase 3 — Parser (3h)

- [ ] AST node dataclasses in `ast_nodes.py`: `Recipe`, `PantryDecl`, `Step`, `Quantity`, `Duration`, `KwArg`, `Ident`
- [ ] Recursive-descent parser in `parser.py`
- [ ] One method per grammar rule: `parse_recipe`, `parse_pantry`, `parse_step`, `parse_arglist`, `parse_arg`, `parse_value`
- [ ] Helpful syntax errors with line numbers
- [ ] `test_parser.py`: parses all 3 example recipes; rejects 5+ malformed inputs
- **Checkpoint:** `pad_thai.wok` parses to a complete AST. Commit.

### Phase 4 — Interpreter (3h)

- [ ] `Environment` class wrapping the pantry dict
- [ ] `Interpreter.run(recipe: Recipe)` dispatches each step to the verb table
- [ ] Verb table maps name → callable from `stdlib.py`
- [ ] Each verb resolves its args from the environment, prints a Rich status line, updates state if needed
- [ ] `test_interpreter.py`: full run of `pad_thai.wok` produces expected output; bad recipes raise the right errors
- **Checkpoint:** `wok run recipes/pad_thai.wok` runs end-to-end. Commit.

### Phase 5 — Polish (1h)

- [ ] All 3 example recipes execute cleanly
- [ ] Pretty error rendering (Rich `Panel`, with source snippet + caret)
- [ ] README with: install steps, full `pad_thai.wok` source, screenshot or asciicast of output, language reference
- [ ] `--version`, `--help` are good
- **Checkpoint:** README is shareable. Commit. Done.

